## 1. Define Cover Page Templates (data/style)

Create a new object `CoverTemplates` in commands.js defining ~6 designs. Each template object contains:
- `name`: Template display name (e.g., "Banded")
- `html`: HTML string with placeholder structure (safely escaped, using WC.escapeHtml for dynamic parts)
- `styles`: Optional class name or inline style blocks appended to the template

Example template structure (Banded—simple horizontal bar design):
```javascript
{
  name: "Banded",
  html: `<div style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;min-height:100vh;background:#fff;padding:96px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center">
    <div style="width:100%;height:4px;background:#2b579a;margin-bottom:40px"></div>
    <h1 class="doc-title" style="margin:0;text-align:center;font-size:36pt">Dissertation Title</h1>
    <p style="text-align:center;font-size:14pt;color:#666;margin:20pt 0">Subtitle or Tagline</p>
    <div style="margin-top:auto;text-align:center">
      <p style="margin:8pt 0;font-size:11pt"><b>Author Name</b></p>
      <p style="margin:8pt 0;font-size:11pt;color:#888">${new Date().getFullYear()}</p>
    </div>
    <div style="width:100%;height:2px;background:#2b579a;margin-top:40px"></div>
  </div><p><br></p>`
}
```

Template 1: **Banded** (horizontal accent bars top/bottom, centered text)
Template 2: **Facet** (tilted geometric shapes, left-aligned title, accent color #2B579A)
Template 3: **Filigree** (decorative corner elements, centered elegant layout)
Template 4: **Ion** (minimal, centered with large title, soft background color #F0F0F0)
Template 5: **Motion** (diagonal stripe accent, left-aligned, modern feel)
Template 6: **Retrospect** (large image-like gradient background, layered text)

All templates must:
- Respect --page-w (816px), --page-margin (96px), --page-h (1056px) via 100vh fallback or explicit calc
- Use web-safe fonts (Calibri, Arial, Georgia, etc.) only
- Include editable placeholder text with placeholder class or data attribute for visual hint
- Include a manual page break (class="manual-break") so subsequent content starts on page 2
- Use inline styles (SVG, gradients, box-shadow OK since Chromium 31)

## 2. Implement coverPage Handler (in commands.js)

Add handler: `H.coverPage = (c, node) => coverPageMenu(node);`

Create `coverPageMenu(node)` function:
```javascript
function coverPageMenu(node) {
  WC.flyout(node, (fly) => {
    fly.appendChild(WC.flyHeader('Built-in cover page designs'));
    // Loop through template names
    CoverTemplates.forEach((tmpl) => {
      fly.appendChild(WC.flyItem(tmpl.name, { 
        onClick: () => insertCoverPage(tmpl) 
      }));
    });
    fly.appendChild(WC.flySep());
    fly.appendChild(WC.flyItem('Remove Current Cover Page', { 
      onClick: () => removeCurrentCoverPage() 
    }));
  });
}
```

## 3. Insert Logic (insertCoverPage function)

```javascript
function insertCoverPage(template) {
  WC.closeFlyouts();
  // Move cursor to very beginning
  const sel = window.getSelection();
  const range = document.createRange();
  range.setStart(E().node, 0);
  range.collapse(true);
  sel.removeAllRanges();
  sel.addRange(range);

  // Insert template HTML at start
  E().insertHTML(template.html);

  // Mark document dirty and repaginate
  E().dirty = true;
  E().repaginate();
  E().updateStatus();
  WC.toast('Cover page inserted. Edit placeholder text as needed.');
}
```

## 4. Remove Logic (removeCurrentCoverPage function)

```javascript
function removeCurrentCoverPage() {
  WC.closeFlyouts();
  // Find the first manual-break element (the cover page)
  const coverBreak = E().node.querySelector('.manual-break');
  if (!coverBreak) {
    WC.toast('No cover page found.');
    return;
  }

  // Remove the cover page and its preceding content up to the break
  // Walk backward from the break and remove all siblings until we've removed one full page
  let node = coverBreak.previousSibling;
  while (node) {
    const next = node.previousSibling;
    node.remove();
    node = next;
    // Stop once we've removed the break itself
    if (node === coverBreak) break;
  }
  coverBreak.remove();

  // Also remove the following <p><br></p> if it exists
  const nextP = coverBreak.nextSibling;
  if (nextP && nextP.tagName === 'P' && nextP.textContent.trim() === '') {
    nextP.remove();
  }

  E().dirty = true;
  E().repaginate();
  E().updateStatus();
  WC.toast('Cover page removed.');
}
```

