No changes needed to ribbon-data.js—the control is defined; we just populate the dropdown via the handler.

## 7. Edge Cases & Robustness

- **Empty document:** Cover page inserts at start (before any existing <p><br></p>).
- **Multiple cover pages:** The current impl only finds the first one to remove. Consider restricting via UI state or warning if multiple detected.
- **Placeholder editing:** Placeholders are just editable text in spans/divs—no special behavior needed. Users select and type.
- **Undo/Redo:** Handled transparently by contenteditable's built-in undo. insertHTML is a single undoable action.
- **PDF export:** Cover page is part of the document HTML, so Chromium will export it as pages 1+. No special handling needed.

PHASE 1: Command Handler & Flyout Navigation
1.1 Add H.shapes handler in commands.js that opens a cascading flyout (similar to textEffectsMenu structure).
1.2 Define a SHAPES library keyed by category (string-based nested object: { "Lines": { "line": {...}, "arrow": {...} }, "Rectangles": { "rect": {...}, ... } }) containing shape metadata: id, label, svgPath (or generator function), defaultW, defaultH.
1.3 Build the flyout UI: outer menu lists categories as items; each item's onClick opens a submenu showing shape thumbnails in a 4-column grid. Thumbnails are small SVG previews (40x40px, scaled to fit the path).

PHASE 2: SVG Shape Generator Functions
2.1 Create a ShapeFactory module (in commands.js or a new shapes.js) with generators:
  - line(x1, y1, x2, y2): returns `<svg>...</svg>` with a single <line> element, no fill, stroke="#000", stroke-width="2".
  - rectangle(w, h, rx=0): returns `<svg><rect width="w" height="h" rx="rx" fill="#4472C4" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>`. Default rx=0 for sharp, rx>0 for rounded.
  - ellipse(w, h): `<svg><ellipse cx="w/2" cy="h/2" rx="w/2" ry="h/2" fill="#4472C4" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>`.
  - triangle(w, h): `<svg><polygon points="w/2,0 w,h h,h 0,h" fill="#4472C4" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>`.
  - rightArrow(w, h): `<svg><path d="M0,h/4 L w*0.7,h/4 L w*0.7,0 L w,h/2 L w*0.7,h L w*0.7,h*0.75 L 0,h*0.75 Z" fill="#4472C4" stroke="#000" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>`.
  - star(w, h, points=5): generates a star polygon with 5 points (or n points) centered in the viewBox.
  - callout(w, h, type='speech'): `<svg><rect fill="#4472C4" stroke="#000".../><polygon points="..." for the tail/pointer/</svg>`.

2.2 Each generator accepts (width, height) and returns a complete, inline SVG string with viewBox="0 0 width height" and preserveAspectRatio="none" (so it stretches to the container's size). Use only path/polygon/rect/ellipse/line, no text or <use>.

PHASE 3: Shape Insertion & DOM Structure
3.1 When a shape is selected from the menu, call insertShape(shapeId, shapeConfig). This:
  a. Gets the SVG string from the appropriate generator (e.g., ShapeFactory.rectangle(150, 100)).
  b. Wraps it in a container: `<div class="shape-wrapper" contenteditable="false" data-shape-id="..." style="display:inline-block;width:150px;height:100px;position:relative;margin:4px;border:1px solid #999;user-select:none;"><svg>...</svg><div class="shape-resize-handle" style="position:absolute;bottom:0;right:0;width:8px;height:8px;background:#999;cursor:se-resize"></div></div>&nbsp;`.
  c. Inserts this into the editor via E().insertHTML(...).
  d. Attaches event listeners to the shape-wrapper and resize handle for mouse interactions.

3.2 Shape wrapper properties:
  - contenteditable="false": prevents accidental text editing inside.
  - data-shape-id: tracks the shape type for later formatting.
  - position:relative on wrapper to anchor the resize handle.
  - border and corner handle visual feedback.
  - margin: 4px for breathing room in the text flow.
  - user-select: none to prevent text selection when dragging.

PHASE 4: Resize Functionality
4.1 Attach mousedown listener to the resize handle. On mousedown:
  a. Capture the initial position (mouse.clientX, mouse.clientY) and the wrapper's current (width, height).
  b. Calculate the aspect ratio (AR = w / h).
  c. Attach mousemove and mouseup listeners to document (to capture motion outside the shape).

4.2 On mousemove, calculate deltaX = currentMouseX - startMouseX, deltaY = currentMouseY - startMouseY. Update wrapper width/height; preserve aspect ratio if Shift is held, otherwise allow free resize.
  - New width = Math.max(40, startWidth + deltaX) (minimum 40px to prevent collapse).
  - New height = Math.max(30, startHeight + deltaY).
  - If Shift: new height = new width / AR (or new width = new height * AR, pick one).
  - Update the wrapper's CSS and re-render (no need to re-gen SVG; viewBox handles scaling).

4.3 On mouseup, detach mousemove/mouseup listeners. Mark the document as dirty and call E().repaginate().

PHASE 5: Fill Color & Basic Formatting
5.1 On double-click of the shape, open a small color picker flyout (reuse WC.colorPalette from existing code).
5.2 Get the <svg> element inside the wrapper. Query all fill-able elements (<rect>, <polygon>, <ellipse>, <path with fill>) and update their fill attribute to the selected color.
5.3 Store the fill color in a data attribute (data-fill="#...") on the wrapper for persistence if the document is re-opened (not strictly necessary for MVP).

PHASE 6: Shape Selection & Deletion
6.1 Clicking on the shape-wrapper adds a 'selected' class (border color changes to blue, maybe a subtle shadow).
6.2 Pressing Delete removes the wrapper from the DOM. Ctrl+C copies the wrapper's HTML to clipboard. Ctrl+X cuts it.
6.3 Optional: Implement shape copy/paste by capturing insertHTML within the paste handler to detect shape-wrapper elements and preserve their structure.

