## 2. ONLINE VIDEO (Feasible: Partial — CSP blocks iframes; use thumbnail + clickable link)

### Overview
Current CSP (`default-src 'self'`) blocks iframes and external scripts. True embedded playback is infeasible without relaxing CSP (security risk). **Realistic alternative:** Insert a clickable thumbnail linking to the video URL, with a play-button overlay, styled to look like an embedded player.

### Renderer Handler (`commands.js`)
```javascript
H.onlineVideo = () => WC.Dialogs.onlineVideo();
```

### Dialog Implementation (`dialogs.js` - new `D.onlineVideo`)
- Input field for URL (YouTube, Vimeo, etc.)
- Preview thumbnail (extracted from URL metadata or fetched via open APIs)
- Inserts a clickable `<div>` with background image, play icon overlay, that links to the video

```javascript
D.onlineVideo = function () {
  const urlInput = el('input', { type: 'url', placeholder: 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=...', class: 'grow' });
  const preview = el('div', { style: { width: '200px', height: '112px', background: '#000', borderRadius: '4px', marginTop: '8px', position: 'relative', cursor: 'pointer' } });
  const playBtn = el('div', { html: WC.icon('play_circle', 48), style: { position: 'absolute', top: '50%', left: '50%', transform: 'translate(-50%,-50%)', color: '#fff', opacity: 0.8 } });
  preview.appendChild(playBtn);

  const body = el('div', {}, [
    el('div', { class: 'row' }, [el('label', { text: 'Video URL:', style: { width: '80px' } }), urlInput]),
    el('div', { text: 'Preview:' }),
    preview,
  ]);

  WC.dialog({ title: 'Insert Online Video', width: '420px', body, footer: [
    { label: 'Insert', primary: true, onClick: () => {
      const url = urlInput.value.trim();
      if (!url) return;
      const safeUrl = WC.safeUrl(url);
      const thumb = preview.style.backgroundImage ? preview.style.backgroundImage.replace(/^url\(["']?([^"']*)["']?\)$/, '$1') : '';
      const html = `<a href="${WC.escapeHtml(safeUrl)}" style="display:inline-block;text-decoration:none;position:relative;width:240px;height:134px;background:url('${thumb}') center/cover;border-radius:4px;opacity:0.9">
        <span style="position:absolute;top:50%;left:50%;transform:translate(-50%,-50%);color:#fff;font-size:48px">▶</span>
      </a>&nbsp;`;
      E().insertHTML(html);
    } },
    { label: 'Cancel' },
  ] });

  // On URL input, fetch thumbnail (simple YT extraction or pass-through URL)
  urlInput.addEventListener('change', async () => {
    const url = urlInput.value.trim();
    if (url.includes('youtube.com') || url.includes('youtu.be')) {
      const vid = url.match(/(?:youtube\.com\/watch\?v=|youtu\.be\/)([^&?\/]+)/)?.[1];
      if (vid) preview.style.backgroundImage = `url('https://img.youtube.com/vi/${vid}/0.jpg')`;
    } else if (url.includes('vimeo.com')) {
      // Vimeo requires API call; for simplicity, show a placeholder or skip
      preview.style.backgroundImage = "url('data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22 width=%22240%22 height=%22134%22%3E%3Crect fill=%22%23555%22 width=%22240%22 height=%22134%22/%3E%3Ctext fill=%22%23fff%22 x=%2250%25%22 y=%2250%25%22 text-anchor=%22middle%22 dominant-baseline=%22middle%22%3E[Vimeo]%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E')";
    }
  });
};
```

### Why This Works
- No CSP relaxation needed (all content is `data:` or safe external images/links).
- Looks professional: clickable thumbnail with play button.
- Opens video in the system browser on click (via OS shell or in-app handler).
- Saves and exports cleanly (just an `<a>` tag in the HTML).

### Optional Future Enhancement
If CSP is relaxed to allow `frame-src https://www.youtube.com` and `frame-src https://player.vimeo.com`, true embedded playback can be added. But the current approach is safer and avoids external script injection.

