## 3. OBJECT (Feasible: Partial — true OLE is infeasible; spec "Text from File" as main feature)

### Overview
True OLE (Object Linking & Embedding) requires COM/ActiveX infrastructure and the ability to instantiate Office objects in the Electron process — not feasible in Electron.

**Realistic subset:**
- **"Object..." dropdown item** → Not Implemented (placeholder: toast or stub)
- **"Text from File..." → Real, working feature**: open a file dialog, read the text content (plain text, markdown, HTML, CSV), and insert it into the document.

### Renderer Handler (`commands.js`)
```javascript
H.object = (c, node) => WC.Commands.dropdown(c, node);
// Generic dropdown handler in Commands.dropdown() will route to:
// "Object..." → WC.notImplemented('Object embed')
// "Text from File..." → objectTextFromFile()

function objectTextFromFile() {
  (async () => {
    const r = await window.wordAPI.pickTextFile();
    if (r && r.ok) {
      const p = el('p', { style: { borderLeft: '3px solid #ccc', paddingLeft: '12px', color: '#555', margin: '8px 0', fontStyle: 'italic' }, html: `<strong>[Inserted from ${WC.escapeHtml(r.name)}]</strong><br>${WC.escapeHtml(r.text).replace(/\n/g, '<br>')}` });
      E().insertHTML(p.outerHTML);
    }
  })();
}
```

### Main Process IPC Handler (`main.js`)

```javascript
ipcMain.handle('fs:readTextFile', async () => {
  const res = await dialog.showOpenDialog(mainWindow, {
    title: 'Insert Text from File',
    properties: ['openFile'],
    filters: [
      { name: 'Text & Docs', extensions: ['txt', 'md', 'html', 'htm', 'csv', 'json'] },
      { name: 'All Files', extensions: ['*'] },
    ],
  });
  if (res.canceled || !res.filePaths[0]) return { ok: false, canceled: true };
  const p = res.filePaths[0];
  try {
    const text = await fsp.readFile(p, 'utf8');
    return { ok: true, text, name: path.basename(p) };
  } catch (e) {
    return { ok: false, error: String(e) };
  }
});
```

### Preload Bridge (`preload.js`)
```javascript
pickTextFile: () => ipcRenderer.invoke('fs:readTextFile'),
```

### Result
When a user selects "Text from File…", the inserted content appears as a styled block quote with a note "[Inserted from filename.txt]". Clean, auditable, and works reliably. Exported/saved as plain HTML.

